He therefore that would like as God likes, and condemn as God
condemns, must have neither the eyes of the Papist nor the Protestant;
he must like no truth the less because Ignatius Loyola or John Bunyan
were very zealous for it, nor have the less aversion to any error,
because Dr Trapp or George Fox had brought it forth.
